This module provides utilities for interacting with the GitHub App API, primarily for authentication and managing installations.

## Key Exports

*   **`getInstallationToken(installationId: number)`**: Retrieves an OAuth token for a specific GitHub App installation.
*   **`getInstallationLogin(installationId: number)`**: Fetches the login name (username or organization name) associated with a GitHub App installation.
*   **`deleteInstallation(installationId: number)`**: Deletes a GitHub App installation. **Use with caution.**

## Usage Example

```typescript
import { getInstallationToken, getInstallationLogin } from './lib/github-app';

async function example() {
  const installationId = 12345; // Replace with a valid installation ID

  try {
    const token = await getInstallationToken(installationId);
    console.log('Installation Token:', token);

    const login = await getInstallationLogin(installationId);
    console.log('Installation Login:', login);

    // To delete an installation (use with extreme caution):
    // await deleteInstallation(installationId);
    // console.log('Installation deleted.');

  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error interacting with GitHub App:', error);
  }
}

example();
```

